main trunk line
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the railway line between Auckland and Wellington, less frequently between Picton and Dunedin/Invercargill
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Geoff Robinson on Morning Report recently (7/6/2001) was heard to talk about Auckland, Wellington & Christchurch being on the Main Trunk Line in reference to air transport
